I believe this way it would be more easy to read through:
```python
@staticmethod
def _correct_for_past(date, delta, default):
    if settings.PREFER_DATES_FROM != 'past':
        return date

    if date - delta < default <= delta:
        date = date - delta
    return date

@staticmethod
def _correct_for_future(date, delta, default):
    if settings.PREFER_DATES_FROM != 'future':
        return date

    if date <= default < date + delta:
        date = date + delta
    return date
```

