@eoogbe is correct. This GAX code is a library that we publish ([`google-gax`](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/google-gax)), and it's already a dependency for the generated GAPIC code for each API.

For auto-gen, I generally copy the code from `artman/output/gcloud-...` to the repo where I want it using `cp -rf artman/output/gcloud-... target_dir`. That shouldn't clobber anything except for conflicting filenames (of which there shouldn't be any).

BTW, you only need the `google/` sub-directory from the generated GAPIC LRO code. The rest is package meta-data that we don't need, since `gax-python` already has its own package metadata. However, you should check that we have all the same dependencies, path declarations, etc. from `setup.py`.
